 where a fiducial value of $\tau_{\mathrm{SF}}=1.5\mathrm{Gyr}$ is assumed for the molecular gas depletion time scale. The delayed cooling model \citep{sims:sdqg09,sims:gbmb10,sims:atm11,sims:bsgk12,sims:aklg13,sims:sbmw13} is implemented as the stellar feedback recipe in the simulations to reduce star formation rate and therefore produce galaxies with relatively realistic properties for most of the redshift range of interest.

